{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Age had a positive impact on screening with each additional year in age increasing the probability of screening slightly (OR 1.01 95% CI 1-1.01).",
    "Males had lower screening rates in our cohort (OR 0.82 95% CI 0.73-0.91).",
    "The life events with the most negative impact were arrest or incarceration (OR 0.26 95% CI 0.06-0.77), becoming homeless (OR 0.18 95% CI 0.01-0.92), separation from spouse or partner (OR 0.32 95% CI 0.05-1.18), married or starting to live with a partner (OR 0.6 95% CI 0.19-1.53), although latter events had relatively low statistical significance due to a small number of detected events.",
    "Death of somebody close to the patient (excluding spouse) increased the chance of screening, although the effect was not statistically significant (OR 1.21 95% CI 0.71-2.05).",
    "Other events, such as divorce, death of spouse, and critical illness did not appear to have effect on screening adherence."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}